{"word":"αὔριον","slug":"αὔριον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αὔριον</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>akin to <a href='S:ἠώς'><el>ἠώς</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to-morrow</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>cras</el>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἐς αὔριον</el> <i>on the morrow</i> or <i>till morning</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <i>the morrow</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; in attic, <el>ἡ αὔριον</el> (<a href='S:scilicet'>sc.</a> <el>ἡμέρα</el>) <i>the morrow</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <el>ἡ αὔρ. ἡμέρα</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <el>ἡ ἐς αὔρ. ἡμέρα</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>ὁ αὔριον χρόνος</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}